      {
        "id": 1815131,
        "name": "Robert Sand",
        "username": "Robert_Sand",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/r/9e8a1a/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2015-12-16T18:39:16.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"William Kelley\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n William Kelley:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>In my experience I\u2019d tentatively suggest that 2006 was one of Coche\u2019s less successful vintages, with the wines lacking just a bit of their usual magic. Would be interested to hear what others have to say.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>In my humble experience Coche\u00b4s wines need a lot of air - it might be that 2006 has slightly less vital acidity than (e.g.) 2007 or 2005 - BTW just like other white Burgs, but the 06 Village showed such impressive weight and back palate (for a Village) that I would never say \u201cless successful\u201d, simply different due to the vintage.</p>",
